> A cond expression with non-exhaustive arms.
> The arms cover scores above 50 and below 10, but leave the range
> 10 <= score < 50 uncovered. The checker reports a counterexample.
module NonExhaustiveCond.

Priority.
score p: Priority => Nat.
tier p: Priority => Nat.
---
all p: Priority | tier p = cond score p >= 50 => 2, score p < 10 => 0.
